<h5>Ideation</h5>
<p>Based on the needs and goals of my users, I created a user flow. The user flow helped me to identify what information would be need to be presented or interacted with by the user at each stage of the user journey.</p> 
<p>At an early stage of creating a user flow map, I was able to determine that the best solution for the critical problems identified would be a web based solution. This was due to the reasons that it would match with user expectations to ‘search online’.</p>
<p>I experimented with different user flows to produce one which would be most effective to complete the user’s task. Throughout the iterative process, I tested different flows with users to identify the one which would allow the completion of the task most effectively and efficiently. I did this through showing users high-fidelity designs which I created in Figma. Creating a high-fidelity design at this stage, allowed me to gain richer insights into the errors users were making in the different flows. This was essential to help develop red routes and thus identifying the optimum user flow.</p>
